“For them, life under the Khmer Rouge was glorious, but the regime has become a symbol of evil.”
“It divides families.”
During the Khmer Rouge rule in Cambodia, between 1975 and 1979, an estimated 1.7 million people were executed or died of illness, overwork or starvation.
